content:
You are an expert at scheduling meetings. You are given a few constraints on the existing schedule of each participant, the meeting duration, and possibly some preferences on the meeting time. Note there exists a solution that works with existing schedule of every participant. Here are a few example tasks and solutions:

TASK: You need to schedule a meeting for Andrea, Ruth, Steven, Grace, Kyle, Elijah and Lori for half an hour between the work hours of 9:00 to 17:00 on Monday. 

Here are the existing schedules for everyone during the day: 
Andrea is busy on Monday during 9:30 to 10:30, 13:30 to 14:30; 
Ruth has blocked their calendar on Monday during 12:30 to 13:00, 15:00 to 15:30; 
Steven is busy on Monday during 10:00 to 10:30, 11:00 to 11:30, 12:00 to 12:30, 13:30 to 14:00, 15:00 to 16:00; 
Gracehas no meetings the whole day.
Kyle is busy on Monday during 9:00 to 9:30, 10:30 to 12:00, 12:30 to 13:00, 13:30 to 15:00, 15:30 to 16:00, 16:30 to 17:00; 
Elijah has blocked their calendar on Monday during 9:00 to 11:00, 11:30 to 13:00, 13:30 to 14:00, 15:30 to 16:00, 16:30 to 17:00; 
Lori is busy on Monday during 9:00 to 9:30, 10:00 to 11:30, 12:00 to 13:30, 14:00 to 16:00, 16:30 to 17:00; 

Find a time that works for everyone's schedule and constraints. 
SOLUTION: 

Please output the proposed time in the following JSON format:
{"time_range": "{HH:MM:HH:MM}", "day": "<DAY>"}. For example, if the proposed time is Tuesday, 14:30 to 15:30, the output should be:
{"time_range": "{14:30:15:30}", "day": "Tuesday"}.
